Old photo but same me 🤗 and I recently saw a 10 things about me introduction post and got inspired to do it myself as it has been quite a while! 

1. I didn’t know anything about rugs when I met hubby Dave in 2009 but I was a photographer and an interior / art lover so the learning of them, the passion for them and the love of capturing them came fast!
2. I fell in love with running a couple years ago but I am a slow one and honestly I’m okay with it 😂🏃🏻‍♀️Despite being slow, I love races and talking about running 🤦🏻‍♀️
3. I never got a certification or degree in interior design but I’ve always had the passion for it, and working with our customers sometimes allows me to flex that which I’m so thankful for! 
4. We have two boys, almost 8 and almost 11, and a dog Evie, in other words: please send help! 😂🤷🏻‍♀️
5. We live and run our business in Katonah, NY, a small + charming town about an hour from NYC and we really love it here ❤️
6. Our last name Dilmaghani is Persian and there is a village in Iran that the name comes from. Dave’s grandfather came to America in the 1920s and brought his own passed down rug business with him.
7. Dave is 5th generation in the rug business and we have just the two of us actually stumbled upon hand-knotted rugs his ancestors had made as early as the 1800s. They used the insignia of a crown - I guess that makes us rug royalty? 👸🫅
8. Yes the “shoe shots” are me - ha and it cracks me up when people think I’m really into shoes (I mean I am to a point) because one of my closest friends has THE craziest and biggest shoe collection I’ve ever seen and I could never come close…
9. I have lupus and honestly I don’t let it define me in any way shape or form but when it challenges me, I transform it merely into a reminder that I never know what the person next to me or stranger on the street is going through….kindness and empathy is always my way forward….
10. I am so thankful for anyone following along and supporting our business! We are so passionate about rugs but more-so, about our customers and it’s what keeps us going. The exciting projects, the perfect one of a kind rug pairing, the relationship, we love it all! ❤️
